<paragraph id="354B36B4564DFFF8D1B7FA25FEA6631C" blockId="81.[108,636,1479,1734]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
VOUCHER MATERIAL (TOTAL = 8): Jenaro 
<collectingRegion id="F730F856564DFFF8D372FA25FF20637F" country="Panama" name="Herrera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">Herrera</collectingRegion>
(AMNH 278467, 278484; CEBIOMAS 110, 111; MUSM 5549), Nuevo 
<collectingRegion id="F730F856564DFFF8D090F9EBFDA6635E" box="[427,529,1545,1569]" country="Trinidad and Tobago" name="San Juan/Laventille" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">San Juan</collectingRegion>
(AMNH 272812; MUSM 13270, 13271); see table 36 for measurements.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B4564DFFF8D1B7F98EFDCB63B9" blockId="81.[108,636,1479,1734]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
UNVOUCHERED OBSERVATIONS: One individual of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D194F96CFEF863DA" box="[175,335,1678,1701]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maresi">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D194F96CFEF863DA" box="[175,335,1678,1701]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">Tonatia maresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(identified as 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D0D3F96CFDC463DA" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[488,627,1677,1701]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D0D3F96CFDC463DA" box="[488,627,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">T. saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was captured and released at Divisor during the
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B4564DFFF8D397FB23FB0A6064" blockId="81.[684,1213,1217,1737]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
Sierra del Divisor Rapid Biological Inventory (Jorge and Velazco, 2006). Another individual was captured at Frog Valley on 
<date id="414A1074564DFFF8D2C1FAE1FB0E6064" box="[1018,1209,1283,1307]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" value="2019-02-17">17 February 2019</date>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B4564DFFFAD3F7FAC6FE166611" blockId="81.[684,1213,1217,1737]" lastBlockId="83.[108,638,226,1738]" lastPageId="83" lastPageNumber="83" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
IDENTIFICATION: The genus 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D520FAC6FBD86044" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1827" box="[1051,1135,1316,1339]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D520FAC6FBD86044" box="[1051,1135,1316,1339]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">Tonatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a complex taxonomic history. Up until 2002, this genus was thought to include six or seven species, but Lee et al. (2002) demonstrated that these did not comprise a monophyletic group and transferred most of them to the genus 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D397FA08FC82637D" box="[684,821,1514,1538]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D397FA08FC86637D" authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1836" box="[684,817,1514,1538]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Thymelaeaceae" genus="Lophostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Lophostoma</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
restricting 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D28CFA09FBBE637D" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1827" box="[951,1033,1515,1538]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D28CFA09FBBE637D" box="[951,1033,1515,1538]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">Tonatia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to just the 
<typeStatus id="EA4F8816564DFFF8D5B6FA09FB0B637C" box="[1165,1212,1515,1539]" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">type</typeStatus>
species (
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D231F9EEFCDA635C" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[778,877,1547,1571]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D231F9EEFCAD635C" box="[778,794,1548,1571]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D212F9E9FCDA635C" box="[809,877,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and its close relative, 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D554F9EEFD4E633B" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D554F9EEFBC8635C" box="[1135,1151,1548,1571]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D5B5F9EEFD4E633B" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Previously, the name 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D538F9CEFBFE633B" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[1027,1097,1580,1604]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D538F9CEFBFE633B" box="[1027,1097,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been applied to all living members of the latter group, but Williams et al. (1995) had shown that it includes two species, with 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564DFFF8D2EBF972FB8763D8" baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[976,1072,1679,1703]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="81" pageNumber="81" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bidens">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564DFFF8D2EBF972FB8763D8" box="[976,1072,1679,1703]" italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">T. bidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
restricted to the Atlantic Forest (southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564DFFF8D51EF953FBD063B6" box="[1061,1127,1713,1737]" name="Brazil" pageId="81" pageNumber="81">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, north- eastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD1E9FF00FEFF6585" box="[210,328,226,250]" name="Argentina" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, and eastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD338FF00FDC76585" box="[515,624,226,250]" name="Paraguay" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
), whereas the name 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD00EFEE1FE776464" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[309,448,259,283]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD00EFEE1FE776464" box="[309,448,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">T. saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(originally based on Jamaican fossil material) applied to populations in 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD1EAFEA7FE926422" box="[209,293,325,349]" name="Mexico" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Central America, the Caribbean, and northern South America. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD31CFE85FF6C64E0" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD31CFE85FF6C64E0" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Tonatia saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
thus conceived included three subspecies: 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD199FE4BFEA064BF" box="[162,279,424,448]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
T. s. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD1EFFE4AFEA064BF" authorityName="Webster and Jones" authorityYear="1987" box="[212,279,424,448]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Glossophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bakeri">bakeri</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD01FFE4BFE2A64BF" box="[292,413,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
T. s. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD06DFE4BFE2A64BF" box="[342,413,425,448]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maresi">maresi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD0E1FE4BFDCB64BF" box="[474,636,424,448]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">
T. s. 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD337FE4AFDCB64BF" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[524,636,424,448]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">saurophila</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(see Williams et al., 1995; Williams and Genoways, 2008). Most recently, Basantes et al. (2020) conducted thorough morphological, morphometric, and molecular analyses of this group and concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD022FDACFE11671A" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[281,422,589,613]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD022FDACFE11671A" box="[281,422,589,613]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">T. saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as defined by Williams et al. (1995) is a complex that includes three valid species: 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD005FD72FDB067D8" authorityName="Koopman and Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[318,519,655,679]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD005FD72FDB067D8" box="[318,519,655,679]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Tonatia saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be an extinct island form, whereas living populations formerly referred to that species represent either 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD18FFD11FEAF6675" box="[180,280,755,778]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maresi">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD18FFD11FEAF6675" box="[180,280,755,778]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">T. maresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(east of the Andes) or 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564FFFFAD327FD11FDCB6674" authorityName="Webster and Jones" authorityYear="1987" box="[540,636,755,779]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Glossophaga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="83" pageNumber="83" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bakeri">
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564FFFFAD327FD11FDCB6674" box="[540,636,755,779]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">T. bakeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(from southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD05AFCF6FE036653" box="[353,436,788,812]" name="Mexico" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Mexico</collectingCountry>
southward into northern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD1E5FCD7FEF96632" box="[222,334,821,845]" name="Colombia" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD33FFCD7FDCF6632" box="[516,632,821,845]" name="Venezuela" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="4DE37624564FFFFAD00EFCB4FE216611" box="[309,406,854,878]" name="Ecuador" pageId="83" pageNumber="83">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="618B663C564EFFFBD150F9D9FBB96310" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5415376" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5415376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5415376/files/figure.png" pageId="82" pageNumber="82" startId="82.[107,149,1595,1616]" targetBox="[179,1139,224,1568]" targetPageId="82">
<paragraph id="354B36B4564EFFFBD150F9D9FBB96310" blockId="82.[107,1211,1593,1647]" pageId="82" pageNumber="82">
FIG. 20. Photographs of 
<emphasis id="0780EAA6564EFFFBD05CF9DBFEC8632E" bold="true" box="[359,383,1593,1617]" pageId="82" pageNumber="82">A,</emphasis>
an adult male (ROM 122096) 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D37564EFFFBD381F9D8FCF8632E" box="[698,847,1594,1617]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="maresi">
